1
00:00:03,031 --> 00:00:05,154
A radiation machine gave one patient roughly

2
00:00:05,154 --> 00:00:07,277
100 times the intended dose.

3
00:00:08,259 --> 00:00:10,343
The manufacturer said it was impossible.

4
00:00:11,224 --> 00:00:12,105
Then it happened again.

5
00:00:12,147 --> 00:00:14,851
The Therac-25 replaced physical safety interlocks

6
00:00:14,851 --> 00:00:17,555
with software checks.

7
00:00:18,436 --> 00:00:20,610
During fast data entry, a race condition

8
00:00:20,610 --> 00:00:22,784
could leave the machine in the wrong

9
00:00:22,784 --> 00:00:24,958
state and fire a full power beam

10
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:27,132
with no filter.

11
00:00:27,111 --> 00:00:29,175
Nobody caught it because the code had

12
00:00:29,175 --> 00:00:31,240
been reused from older machines, and reused

13
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,304
code felt like tested code.

14
00:00:34,246 --> 00:00:35,710
Operators reported errors.

15
00:00:36,610 --> 00:00:39,838
The manufacturer insisted the machine was safe.

16
00:00:39,936 --> 00:00:41,541
More patients were burned before the pattern

17
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:43,146
was treated as real.

18
00:00:43,185 --> 00:00:46,215
The disaster was not just bad code.

19
00:00:46,896 --> 00:00:48,787
It was a system with no independent

20
00:00:48,787 --> 00:00:50,678
safety layer, no quick way to believe

21
00:00:50,678 --> 00:00:52,568
field reports, and no design for software

22
00:00:52,568 --> 00:00:54,459
being wrong.

23
00:00:55,601 --> 00:00:57,507
That is how small causes become massive

24
00:00:57,507 --> 00:00:59,412
consequences.
